18:05.379 --> 18:10.596
a great judge knows
that he needs to <i>be</i> justice."

18:10.628 --> 18:13.891
Now, I wouldn't be so bold as to
call myself a great judge,

18:13.923 --> 18:17.795
but I do know
that as I sit here today,

18:17.828 --> 18:20.771
I'm thinking about
my granddaddy.

18:20.804 --> 18:23.651
And that's why
I'm gonna direct this verdict

18:23.684 --> 18:28.580
and find this here defendant...
guilty.

18:28.612 --> 18:30.565
Cut!

18:30.596 --> 18:32.324
Alastair, that was terrific.

18:32.356 --> 18:34.660
Terrific?
It was bloody genius.

18:34.692 --> 18:36.484
You're not going
to top that one.

18:36.516 --> 18:38.019
I'll see you all tomorrow then.

18:38.051 --> 18:39.747
Did you hear what I just said?

18:39.779 --> 18:41.635
He's supposed to say
"not guilty."

18:41.667 --> 18:44.579
- He said guilty.
- Fuck.

18:44.611 --> 18:45.925
Could have just told me
I had ass cancer.

18:45.956 --> 18:46.948
Sorry.

18:46.981 --> 18:48.708
- Alastair.
- Yes?

18:48.740 --> 18:51.428
Oh, God,
I hate to do this to you,

18:51.459 --> 18:53.540
but we're gonna have
to do one more.

18:53.572 --> 18:56.388
- The last line is "not guilty."
- "Not guilty."

18:56.420 --> 18:58.019
- What did I say?
- Guilty.

18:58.051 --> 19:00.196
- The fuck I did.
- Yeah, he didn't say that.

19:00.228 --> 19:01.795
Did... I mean,
but really, just please?

19:01.827 --> 19:03.044
No.
I know what I said, love.

19:03.076 --> 19:04.675
So let's just look
at the playback.

19:04.707 --> 19:06.276
He wouldn't have said that.

19:06.308 --> 19:08.643
Can we just see
the playback, please?

19:08.675 --> 19:10.531
You... What are you smirking at?

19:10.563 --> 19:12.515
What? I didn't say anything.

19:12.548 --> 19:14.948
Do you think it's easy
to carry this piece of shit

19:14.980 --> 19:16.708
on my shoulders week after week?

19:16.740 --> 19:18.339
You think I need a twat like you

19:18.372 --> 19:20.099
standing there
hoping I'll cock it up?

19:20.131 --> 19:22.468
How long have you worked
on the show?

19:22.500 --> 19:24.068
It's my first week.

19:24.099 --> 19:26.372
Your first week.
It's his first week, everyone.

19:33.635 --> 19:35.108
God!

19:35.140 --> 19:36.483
<i>And that's why I'm gonna</i>

19:36.515 --> 19:37.732
<i>direct this verdict...</i>

19:37.765 --> 19:39.267
Let that be a lesson to you.

19:39.299 --> 19:41.412
- You good?
- I'm fine.

19:41.444 --> 19:42.436
<i>...guilty.</i>

19:42.468 --> 19:43.525
Let's do this.
Come on.

19:43.556 --> 19:45.572
Let's do it. Let's roll.

19:45.604 --> 19:47.556
Rolling!

19:47.588 --> 19:48.995
Does that happen often?

19:49.028 --> 19:51.076
Sometimes after lunch.

19:51.108 --> 19:53.699
We always put a stunt guy
right there, pay him extra.

19:53.731 --> 19:55.236
Don't tell Alastair.

19:57.220 --> 19:58.212
Ready?

19:58.244 --> 19:59.812
Action.

19:59.845 --> 20:02.275
"...and find
this here defendant

20:02.307 --> 20:04.259
not guilty."

20:04.291 --> 20:07.171
Cut!

20:07.203 --> 20:10.115
Wouldn't be the first time
I've had the clap.

20:22.628 --> 20:25.028
<i>Entrez.</i>

20:25.060 --> 20:27.588
"Not guilty."

20:27.620 --> 20:30.596
Ah, lord of the manor, down to
slum a bit with the vassals.

20:30.628 --> 20:32.195
To what do we owe the honor?

20:32.228 --> 20:34.596
I wanted to introduce you
to Charlie Waldo,

20:34.628 --> 20:36.260
the detective we told you about.

20:36.292 --> 20:38.020
He used to be king shit
at the LAPD.

20:38.052 --> 20:39.940
Ah, the fallen angel.
You've landed him.

20:39.972 --> 20:41.380
Didn't I promise you I would?

20:41.412 --> 20:42.884
I'd give you the shirt
off my back. You know that.

20:42.916 --> 20:44.772
I'd prefer the watch
off your wrist.

20:44.804 --> 20:46.563
Have you seen
what this man wears?

20:46.596 --> 20:48.419
Costs more than the house
I grew up in.

20:48.451 --> 20:51.363
Kudoke Skeleton.
They only make 35 a year.

20:51.396 --> 20:52.836
Maybe I'll make you
a wrap gift of one. How's that?

20:52.868 --> 20:54.724
Can we have that
signed in blood?

20:54.756 --> 20:56.740
"Signed in blood,"
he says.

20:56.772 --> 20:59.236
I'm done for the day, Detective.
Do you have plans?

20:59.268 --> 21:01.092
- Where do you live?
- Idyllwild.

21:01.124 --> 21:03.460
- I'm only here for today.
- Details we're sorting out.

21:03.492 --> 21:05.796
I haven't agreed
to take this case.

21:05.828 --> 21:07.236
I'll find a hotel for tonight.

21:07.268 --> 21:08.579
Nonsense.
You'll stay at my house.

21:08.611 --> 21:09.764
Great idea.

21:09.796 --> 21:11.172
Right to the scene of the crime.

21:11.204 --> 21:12.548
You don't mind sleeping

21:12.580 --> 21:14.307
surrounded by yellow tape,
do you?

21:14.339 --> 21:17.444
This fucking guy.

21:17.476 --> 21:18.564
Come on, Waldo.
What do you say?

21:18.596 --> 21:19.556
What's the worst
that can happen?

21:19.588 --> 21:21.059
Lorena turns up in a day or two,

21:21.091 --> 21:23.971
you can go back
to wherever you came from.

21:24.004 --> 21:26.052
Hell, maybe even get
your reputation back.

21:26.084 --> 21:28.196
Just kidding.

21:35.844 --> 21:39.331
Interest you
in a wee snifter, Detective?

21:39.364 --> 21:41.508
No, thank you.

21:41.540 --> 21:42.820
I deplore drinking alone,

21:42.852 --> 21:44.324
so I'll have a double.

21:47.907 --> 21:50.308
She was so proud of this room.

21:50.340 --> 21:52.100
Chin-chin.

21:52.132 --> 21:55.748
It was in <i>Town and Wanker</i>
magazine, you know.

21:55.780 --> 21:58.403
Why don't you walk me
through that morning?

22:02.084 --> 22:03.812
All right.

22:03.844 --> 22:05.540
One more time.

22:08.131 --> 22:10.148
It was a Saturday.

22:10.180 --> 22:13.891
I woke up... or came to...
in my study,

22:13.924 --> 22:16.804
about a half a mile
down that way.

22:16.836 --> 22:19.812
I realized I had no recollection
of the previous night.

22:19.844 --> 22:23.908
I came in here.
Found my sweet Monica.

22:25.796 --> 22:29.859
I ran back to the kitchen,
dialed 911.

22:29.892 --> 22:33.412
There was a shattered vase.

22:33.444 --> 22:35.300
Anyhow,
when the ambulance arrived,

22:35.332 --> 22:36.996
they told me
she was already gone

22:37.028 --> 22:39.715
and had been
for quite some time.

22:42.212 --> 22:44.964
Does anyone else have keys?

22:44.996 --> 22:47.812
Only Rosario. That's our nanny.

22:47.844 --> 22:50.500
And she was in Venezuela
visiting her family.

22:50.532 --> 22:51.876
Nanny?

22:51.908 --> 22:53.540
You have kids in the house?

22:53.572 --> 22:56.452
Yes.
We have one child, Gaby.

22:56.484 --> 22:58.180
She likely wasn't
the killer either,

22:58.212 --> 23:00.260
but she'll be home
from kindergarten soon enough

23:00.292 --> 23:03.140
if you think it's worth
trying to wrest a confession.

23:03.172 --> 23:05.316
Pretty glib, considering.

23:05.348 --> 23:06.852
Forgive me.

23:06.884 --> 23:09.700
Dear Gaby doesn't even know,
of course, but...

23:11.684 --> 23:14.404
...the world is certain
I murdered my wife, Mr. Waldo,

23:14.436 --> 23:17.796
and I can't even tell you
the world is wrong.

23:17.828 --> 23:20.420
If you know a man who's handled
a similar predicament

23:20.452 --> 23:22.948
with more élan, point me to him,

23:22.980 --> 23:25.860
and I shall gladly emulate.

23:25.891 --> 23:28.132
You ever thought about trying
to stop drinking?

23:31.268 --> 23:34.179
All the time.

23:34.212 --> 23:37.956
But this doesn't seem the week
for that, now, does it?

23:37.988 --> 23:39.331
Daddy!

23:39.364 --> 23:41.540
Princess Ozma,
where did you come from?

23:41.572 --> 23:43.300
Oh, oh, oh.

23:43.332 --> 23:46.436
Want to hear the song Little Dog
taught us at school today?

23:46.468 --> 23:48.868
A little dog?
Why, yes, of course.

23:48.900 --> 23:52.100
♪ Brush every morning,
brush every night ♪

23:52.132 --> 23:56.196
♪ I brush and I brush
so my teeth will be white ♪

23:56.228 --> 23:59.524
♪ Teeth can be shiny,
teeth can be gold ♪

23:59.556 --> 24:03.492
♪ I hope I still have some
when I'm very old ♪

24:04.836 --> 24:06.564
- You know it.
- I do know it, Gaby.

24:06.596 --> 24:10.692
I'd like to meet my new friend,
Mr. Waldo.

24:10.724 --> 24:13.988
He looks scary. Like a lion.

24:14.020 --> 24:15.748
Yeah, but he's a friendly lion.

24:15.780 --> 24:18.884
Gaby and I are going to spend
some daddy time before bed,

24:18.916 --> 24:20.804
you snuggly baby.

24:20.836 --> 24:25.732
Oh, you haven't decided
to take the case yet, have you?

24:25.764 --> 24:27.428
What say you, Detective?

24:27.460 --> 24:30.756
Will you return to your mountain
and leave me to the fates?

24:30.788 --> 24:33.028
Or will you stick around
the shitty of the angels

24:33.060 --> 24:36.612
long enough to see the police
maybe get it right this time?

24:36.644 --> 24:38.403
Whatever right may look like.

24:38.436 --> 24:41.796
Daddy, can Mr. Lion drive
to school with us tomorrow?

24:41.828 --> 24:43.748
Can he please?

24:43.780 --> 24:45.796
Please?

24:47.747 --> 24:49.604
Yay!

24:55.779 --> 24:57.476
Will this be all right?

24:59.684 --> 25:01.091
It's perfect.

25:07.940 --> 25:09.604
Fucking Lorena.

25:32.292 --> 25:35.812
<i>Guilty.</i>

25:35.844 --> 25:37.348
<i>...and turn down the volume
on the media circus.</i>

25:37.380 --> 25:38.627
<i>Oh, come on, Fontella.</i>

25:38.660 --> 25:40.388
<i>You live for the media circus.</i>

25:40.420 --> 25:41.732
<i>Now I'm hearing there could be
an indictment</i>

25:41.763 --> 25:43.140
<i>as early as tomorrow.</i>

25:43.171 --> 25:44.612
<i>We've not been told that.</i>

25:44.643 --> 25:46.020
<i>And now the</i> L.A. Times
<i>is reporting</i>

25:46.051 --> 25:47.396
<i>that sources on the LAPD say</i>

25:47.427 --> 25:49.252
<i>there are no
unidentified fingerprints</i>

25:49.284 --> 25:50.372
<i>anywhere in that room.</i>

25:50.403 --> 25:51.940
<i>What does that suggest to you?</i>

25:51.971 --> 25:53.252
<i>It suggests that
the real killer</i>

25:53.283 --> 25:54.788
<i>knew what he was doing.</i>

25:54.820 --> 25:55.811
<i>You promised us
Charlie Waldo</i>

25:55.844 --> 25:57.219
<i>from the Lydell Lipps case.</i>

25:57.252 --> 25:58.947
<i>What does it say
that he's not here with you?</i>

25:58.980 --> 26:00.804
<i>Charlie Waldo
is busy uncovering...</i>

26:09.284 --> 26:12.900
Welcome to kindergartens
of the rich and famous.

26:12.931 --> 26:15.107
Gaby, Mr. Lion needs to
talk to your teacher.

26:15.140 --> 26:17.700
But first, he's going to
park this beast.

26:17.731 --> 26:19.940
Now get out, little blighter.

26:22.820 --> 26:24.068
Baby back ribs in there.

26:27.395 --> 26:29.540
Alas, poor Yorick!

26:29.572 --> 26:31.524
I knew him, my sweet Gaby,

26:31.556 --> 26:35.171
a fellow of infinite jest,
of most excellent fancy.

26:35.204 --> 26:37.795
He hath borne me on his back
a thousand times,

26:37.828 --> 26:40.132
and now, how abhorred
in my imagination it is!

26:40.164 --> 26:41.891
My gorge rises at it.

26:41.924 --> 26:44.740
Yes, you're a shadow
of your former self.

26:44.771 --> 26:46.212
It's that keto diet I'm on.

26:46.244 --> 26:48.996
I'm starving. I think I may have
taken it a bit too far.

26:49.028 --> 26:50.340
You got anything in your lunch?

26:50.371 --> 26:52.547
Like a pork chop?
Ham sandwich? No?

26:52.580 --> 26:53.700
I'm afraid it
wouldn't do you any good,

26:53.732 --> 26:55.524
dear boy.
I think you're dead.

26:55.556 --> 26:57.251
Dead? That's tragic.

26:57.284 --> 27:00.387
Yes, indeed, it's tragic.

27:00.420 --> 27:02.211
Where be your gibes now?

27:02.244 --> 27:04.771
Your gambols? Your songs?

27:04.804 --> 27:06.084
Your flashes of merriment

27:06.116 --> 27:09.092
that were wont to set the table
on a roar?

27:10.820 --> 27:12.484
I think
I've soiled my britches.

27:12.515 --> 27:15.395
Should I change my nappy?
Oh, it's all squishy.

27:15.428 --> 27:17.315
Bravo!

27:17.348 --> 27:18.627
Oh, yes, thank you, thank you.

27:18.660 --> 27:20.291
That was funny, Daddy.

27:20.324 --> 27:23.460
Yes. That speech
always slays them.

27:23.492 --> 27:25.539
Come. Let's play on the swings.

27:25.573 --> 27:27.971
I believe Mr. Lion
wants to ask Miss White

27:28.004 --> 27:30.212
whether Daddy plays nicely with
the other children.

27:30.243 --> 27:31.907
Off we go.
Let's get to the swings.

27:31.940 --> 27:34.820
- It'll be a swinging time.
- Swing, swing, swing!

27:34.851 --> 27:37.348
My name's Waldo.

27:37.379 --> 27:39.331
I'm a detective
working for Alastair.

27:39.364 --> 27:42.436
Jayne.
My heart breaks for Gaby.

27:42.467 --> 27:46.244
Mr. Pinch is doing a lot
to keep her spirits up.

27:46.276 --> 27:49.251
And Mrs. Pinch...
What was she like as a parent?

27:51.811 --> 27:54.243
Mrs. Pinch?

27:56.740 --> 27:59.108
We have the children memorize
these poems.

27:59.140 --> 28:03.299
I like to ask the kids whose mom
and dad can recite them too.

28:03.331 --> 28:04.707
Half the time
these parents can't,

28:04.740 --> 28:08.612
but the nanny can
in two languages.

28:08.643 --> 28:10.660
What about the Pinches?

28:10.693 --> 28:12.291
Mrs. Pinch never knew them.

28:12.324 --> 28:15.971
Mr. Pinch, always.

28:16.004 --> 28:18.659
That's unusual.

28:18.691 --> 28:20.931
The death must have shocked
the hell out of this place, huh?

28:22.724 --> 28:24.419
Not me.

28:27.428 --> 28:28.707
Good morning, kids.

28:28.740 --> 28:31.204
Okay, everyone find their place.
Get your bunnies.

28:31.235 --> 28:32.995
We're gonna start by writing
your names on the back of them,

28:33.028 --> 28:35.011
so have a marker.

28:35.044 --> 28:38.403
Miss White, I'm gonna need
to talk to you again.

28:38.437 --> 28:39.875
Sure.

28:42.180 --> 28:44.708
Does everyone have their bunny
from yesterday?

28:48.164 --> 28:50.852
Come meet me tonight.
We can talk then.

28:52.868 --> 28:55.204
All right.
Have you got names set?

28:55.235 --> 28:56.740
Yes, Miss White.

29:53.124 --> 29:56.067
Do you put your boots
on your chairs at home?

29:56.100 --> 29:58.403
I live in a trailer
with a chicken.

29:59.811 --> 30:02.724
What happened to this "vayse"?

30:02.756 --> 30:05.540
"Vahse."

30:05.571 --> 30:09.124
Ah, yes. Well...

30:09.155 --> 30:11.331
That's the one
she was killed with.

30:13.284 --> 30:14.819
What was that, ceramic?

30:14.851 --> 30:17.124
Earthenware.
Nice vase. I rather miss it.

30:17.156 --> 30:18.915
What about that table?

30:20.675 --> 30:21.956
It's different.

30:21.987 --> 30:23.907
Monica was a tinkerer.

30:23.941 --> 30:27.620
No room was ever finished
to her satisfaction.

30:27.651 --> 30:31.491
Mm. And that sculpture.

30:31.524 --> 30:33.059
The Bard?

30:33.091 --> 30:34.693
The sculpture.

30:34.724 --> 30:36.517
This.

30:38.084 --> 30:39.971
Ah, dear boy.

30:40.004 --> 30:44.101
That's a Regis Award
for my Richard III.

30:44.132 --> 30:45.604
Did you move it?

30:45.635 --> 30:48.836
I've never been much
for acting trophies.

30:48.868 --> 30:51.748
Monica had that one on display
for sentimental reasons.

30:51.781 --> 30:53.475
That was the production
on which we met.

30:53.507 --> 30:55.075
Really?

30:55.108 --> 30:57.955
Perhaps it's wherever Monica
put my other Regises

30:57.988 --> 31:02.276
or my... People's Choice Award.

31:03.811 --> 31:05.635
Good night, sweet prince.

31:05.668 --> 31:08.132
Flights of angels
sing thee to thy rest.

31:17.348 --> 31:21.059
♪ In the old rugged cross ♪

31:21.091 --> 31:24.613
♪ Stained with blood so divine ♪

31:24.644 --> 31:30.980
♪ A wondrous beauty I see ♪

31:31.011 --> 31:35.588
♪ For 'twas on that old cross ♪

31:35.619 --> 31:39.428
♪ Jesus suffered and died ♪

31:39.459 --> 31:42.467
♪ To pardon and sanctify me ♪

31:42.500 --> 31:46.051
There goes the good girl
kindergarten teacher.

31:46.083 --> 31:50.115
Just wait till I have
a few Maker's in me.

31:50.147 --> 31:53.156
So why weren't you shocked
that Monica Pinch was killed?

31:59.876 --> 32:04.228
Okay, Mr. Waldo.

32:04.259 --> 32:06.275
I have a confession.

32:06.308 --> 32:09.219
Okay.

32:09.251 --> 32:11.108
I've been watching
all this TV coverage

32:11.139 --> 32:12.356
since the murder.

32:15.492 --> 32:16.995
I knew exactly who you were

32:17.027 --> 32:19.011
the minute you walked into
my classroom.

32:19.045 --> 32:21.443
That figures.

32:26.371 --> 32:28.291
Who was Lydell Lipps?

32:28.323 --> 32:31.652
Everyone keeps talking
about Lydell Lipps.

32:38.212 --> 32:40.357
I can usually tell when
someone's messing with me.

32:40.388 --> 32:43.045
You're jamming up my radar.

32:43.076 --> 32:45.603
Maybe your radar's just rusty.

32:48.068 --> 32:49.765
Yeah, maybe.

32:50.084 --> 32:52.228
Here you go.

32:52.259 --> 32:53.892
Thanks.

32:58.628 --> 33:00.260
To whiskey and good hair.

33:13.028 --> 33:14.660
It's been a while.

33:24.227 --> 33:26.147
Okay. If you want to know,
I'll tell you.

33:32.196 --> 33:36.483
11 years ago,
there was a robbery at 7-11.

33:36.515 --> 33:39.908
The girl behind the counter
and two customers

33:39.940 --> 33:41.251
got shot dead.

33:41.283 --> 33:45.059
I turned up a kid
named Donny Lipps.

33:45.091 --> 33:46.372
Leaned on him pretty hard.

33:46.405 --> 33:47.875
It paid off.

33:47.907 --> 33:50.115
He said he was waiting
in the car outside.

33:50.148 --> 33:52.068
And in return for a deal,

33:52.100 --> 33:54.372
he would give me the shooter.

33:54.404 --> 33:57.988
Turns out that was Lydell,
his brother.

33:58.021 --> 34:00.805
Signed, sealed.

34:00.836 --> 34:02.499
My career's off to the races,
right,

34:02.531 --> 34:05.315
and I am on fire with ambition.

34:05.348 --> 34:07.492
Everything's going great.

34:07.525 --> 34:09.732
Cut to years later.

34:09.764 --> 34:11.556
Lydell comes up for parole,

34:11.588 --> 34:14.467
and the prosecutors ask me to
help them prep for the hearing.

34:14.500 --> 34:16.165
So I go see the brother again,

34:16.196 --> 34:17.859
who's in prison himself
at this point.

34:17.891 --> 34:19.748
Three strikes, unrelated.

34:21.635 --> 34:27.556
Only now he tells me that
the original story was bullshit.

34:27.588 --> 34:31.299
He made it up
to get me off his back.

34:35.204 --> 34:36.612
So at that point,

34:36.643 --> 34:38.341
Lydell had been in jail for...

34:38.371 --> 34:42.020
7 years, 3 months, and 16 days.

34:44.260 --> 34:46.594
Well, next thing I learn,

34:46.628 --> 34:49.891
it is a lot harder to get
an innocent man out of jail

34:49.924 --> 34:52.451
than to put a guilty man in.

34:52.484 --> 34:54.851
System isn't designed
to deal with mistakes.

34:54.884 --> 34:58.019
And some individuals aren't,
either.

34:59.907 --> 35:01.540
But I keep pushing.

35:01.572 --> 35:03.044
And I keep pushing

35:03.076 --> 35:04.356
and I keep pushing,

