01:13:19.620 --> 01:13:21.380
You know I'm the only one
in town who doesn't grease

01:13:21.412 --> 01:13:23.204
this motherfuckin'
cocksuckin' motherfucker?

01:13:23.236 --> 01:13:24.868
- Little man...
- Whoa.

01:13:24.900 --> 01:13:27.172
...you... you'd better
watch your mouth

01:13:27.204 --> 01:13:30.788
on days that you're followed
around by that douchebag Eskimo.

01:13:30.820 --> 01:13:32.259
What?

01:13:32.292 --> 01:13:34.980
What the...

01:13:35.012 --> 01:13:38.340
He's an Inuit,
you fuckin' philistine.

01:13:38.371 --> 01:13:39.491
Let's go.

01:13:39.524 --> 01:13:41.476
You got another 24 hours, Waldo.

01:13:41.507 --> 01:13:43.236
Okay.

01:13:43.268 --> 01:13:46.307
Come on.
Let's get you up, Cuppy.

01:13:46.340 --> 01:13:48.196
Oh.

01:13:49.220 --> 01:13:50.532
Hi.

01:13:50.564 --> 01:13:52.388
Do you have a school directory
I can look at

01:13:52.419 --> 01:13:55.844
with the names of the students
in each class and their parents?

01:13:55.876 --> 01:13:57.731
It's for Jayne White.

01:14:03.587 --> 01:14:06.148
Thank you.

01:14:11.204 --> 01:14:13.443
Swag Doggg.

01:14:15.780 --> 01:14:17.668
Jamshidi.

01:14:17.700 --> 01:14:19.172
Listen. I'm on to something.

01:14:19.203 --> 01:14:21.188
What do you know about
Darius Jamshidi and Swag Doggg?

01:14:21.219 --> 01:14:23.780
Are those animated characters?

01:14:23.812 --> 01:14:25.956
They both wanted me to stay
the hell away from your case.

01:14:25.988 --> 01:14:27.876
I went to the school today
and checked the directory.

01:14:27.908 --> 01:14:29.540
They're parents...

01:14:29.572 --> 01:14:31.748
They're parents
in your daughter's class.

01:14:31.779 --> 01:14:33.732
Now, I'm thinking that Monica
could've been into something

01:14:33.764 --> 01:14:35.140
with these other parents

01:14:35.171 --> 01:14:36.964
and one or more of them
wanted her dead.

01:14:36.995 --> 01:14:39.267
Question is, though, what the
fuck is going on in that class?

01:14:39.300 --> 01:14:41.635
Oh, who knows?
Show-and-tell.

01:14:41.668 --> 01:14:43.012
Finger painting. I don't know.

01:14:43.044 --> 01:14:44.804
- Hey! Princess!
- What?

01:14:44.836 --> 01:14:46.820
I'm trying to save your life.
You want to cut the self-pity?

01:14:46.852 --> 01:14:48.484
- Self-pity?
- Look.

01:14:48.515 --> 01:14:50.979
You got a terrific little girl
who already lost her mom.

01:14:51.012 --> 01:14:52.451
Does she have to lose a dad?

01:14:52.484 --> 01:14:53.892
Nobody talks to me that way.

01:14:53.924 --> 01:14:55.748
- And do you know why?
- 'Cause they need the money.

01:14:55.779 --> 01:14:57.603
No, because they know they'll
get a damn good drubbing.

01:14:57.636 --> 01:14:59.236
Put 'em up.
Come on. Your turn, love.

01:14:59.267 --> 01:15:00.324
You'll get a real fight.

01:15:00.356 --> 01:15:01.443
I'm not doing this.

01:15:01.476 --> 01:15:02.980
- Come on.
- I'm not doing this.

01:15:03.011 --> 01:15:04.771
- Alastair, you're too drunk!
- Slippery joker.

01:15:04.804 --> 01:15:06.180
- Alastair...
- Hold still, will you?

01:15:06.212 --> 01:15:08.548
It's not even a fair fight!
You're twice my age!

01:15:08.580 --> 01:15:12.355
Okay. Look. I'm a pacifist,
and I refuse to get involved.

01:15:12.388 --> 01:15:13.636
J...

01:15:13.667 --> 01:15:15.908
Alastair?

01:15:15.939 --> 01:15:17.636
Well earned, sir.

01:15:17.667 --> 01:15:19.268
Have you had enough?

01:15:19.300 --> 01:15:20.580
I've had enough.

01:15:20.612 --> 01:15:23.140
Let's you and I have a drink.
Help me up.

01:15:24.900 --> 01:15:26.436
Oh, you've trimmed the hedges.
Handsome devil.

01:15:28.804 --> 01:15:31.172
You remember
having mates, don't you, Waldo?

01:15:31.203 --> 01:15:33.060
Not like you.

01:15:33.668 --> 01:15:34.787
There you go.

01:15:34.820 --> 01:15:36.676
You were right, of course.

01:15:36.707 --> 01:15:39.299
I <i>am</i> shit-faced.

01:15:39.331 --> 01:15:40.644
More than usual.

01:15:40.676 --> 01:15:42.436
Chin-chin.

01:15:42.467 --> 01:15:46.307
You know what you should have
done when your young man died?

01:15:46.340 --> 01:15:49.924
You should have gone on
an epic two-week pub crawl,

01:15:49.955 --> 01:15:52.835
gotten it all out
of your system.

01:15:54.340 --> 01:15:56.579
To self-pity.
Hm.

01:15:56.611 --> 01:15:59.907
That was a powerful observation
coming from the master.

01:15:59.940 --> 01:16:04.484
You and I are two sides
of the same coin, aren't we?

01:16:04.516 --> 01:16:06.820
And now, here you are,
back among the living

01:16:06.853 --> 01:16:08.740
in a way you weren't
just a week ago.

01:16:08.773 --> 01:16:10.084
Mm.

01:16:10.115 --> 01:16:11.875
- Oh, you see a difference?
- Mm!

01:16:11.908 --> 01:16:14.276
All the difference in the world.

01:16:14.307 --> 01:16:17.027
Dicking refuckulous the way
you confronted me out there.

01:16:17.060 --> 01:16:20.196
You didn't have that in you when
you first shuffled onto my set

01:16:20.228 --> 01:16:23.140
with that rat's nest of a beard
and those dead eyes.

01:16:23.173 --> 01:16:25.604
You've been brought back
to life, mate,

01:16:25.636 --> 01:16:27.973
like so many of us...

01:16:28.004 --> 01:16:31.395
by singular carnal charms.

01:16:35.684 --> 01:16:38.468
Is Jayne keeping the baby?

01:16:38.500 --> 01:16:40.835
I think about her all the time.

01:16:40.868 --> 01:16:42.308
But I haven't thought it right
to telephone,

01:16:42.340 --> 01:16:44.163
given the circumstances.

01:16:44.197 --> 01:16:48.068
And I was such a cad,
especially after she told me.

01:16:48.740 --> 01:16:51.651
But I was married, after all,
and what was I to do?

01:16:51.684 --> 01:16:55.780
And then after the business
with my sweet Monica...

01:16:55.813 --> 01:16:58.211
I'm tired, Waldo.

01:17:00.420 --> 01:17:04.196
Fearing that you may not be
as good as others believe.

01:17:04.227 --> 01:17:05.699
It's common to all men.

01:17:06.884 --> 01:17:11.620
But fearing that deep down
you may be a monster...

01:17:12.707 --> 01:17:15.491
...that's a whole different
flavor of hell.

01:17:31.140 --> 01:17:32.964
<i>Ladies and gentlemen,</i>

01:17:32.996 --> 01:17:34.787
<i>we are about to begin.</i>

01:17:34.820 --> 01:17:36.964
<i>Please find your seats.</i>

01:17:46.948 --> 01:17:48.517
Hey.

01:17:49.412 --> 01:17:50.819
Hey.

01:17:52.227 --> 01:17:54.308
You should have told me
about you and Alastair.

01:17:55.011 --> 01:17:57.924
There's nothing to tell.
He's a kindergarten dad.

01:18:04.420 --> 01:18:06.500
Don't worry. It's not Alastair.
It's me.

01:18:07.717 --> 01:18:09.284
I found this burner
in his house.

01:18:09.315 --> 01:18:11.300
On the night his wife died,
he texted back and forth

01:18:11.331 --> 01:18:13.795
with someone, inviting her over.

01:18:13.828 --> 01:18:17.317
Someone... who said
she'd be right there.

01:18:19.076 --> 01:18:21.124
Come on.

01:18:21.157 --> 01:18:22.564
Let's talk.

01:18:28.004 --> 01:18:30.404
Did you have a thing
with Swag Doggg too?

01:18:31.395 --> 01:18:32.963
Yes.

01:18:33.380 --> 01:18:36.195
And that crazy rich guy
Jamshidi?

01:18:39.107 --> 01:18:40.804
You know,
I've been getting beaten up

01:18:40.835 --> 01:18:43.684
and threatened all week
because of you.

01:18:43.715 --> 01:18:45.157
It had nothing to do
with Monica Pinch.

01:18:45.188 --> 01:18:46.691
It was a bunch of rich guys

01:18:46.724 --> 01:18:48.644
that didn't want their affairs
with you exposed.

01:18:48.675 --> 01:18:50.499
What do you want, Waldo?

01:18:50.531 --> 01:18:53.828
I'm a thrill-seeker, and I'm
teaching fucking kindergarten.

01:18:53.860 --> 01:18:56.291
And what could be a bigger rush
than sleeping with the detective

01:18:56.324 --> 01:18:58.660
investigating a death
you're involved in?

01:18:59.300 --> 01:19:01.059
It wasn't just that.

01:19:02.084 --> 01:19:04.164
I really felt something.

01:19:07.684 --> 01:19:09.604
Start from the beginning.

01:19:09.635 --> 01:19:11.108
And no bullshit.

01:19:14.053 --> 01:19:16.868
I was hoping that he would leave
his wife.

01:19:16.900 --> 01:19:20.068
But he was an asshole,
and he kept talking about

01:19:20.099 --> 01:19:23.524
how she wanted him to move back
to England with her.

01:19:23.557 --> 01:19:27.301
Like, he didn't give a shit
about what I was telling him.

01:19:27.332 --> 01:19:30.915
And after that,
total radio silence.

01:19:30.947 --> 01:19:35.395
But I kept texting him,
which was... probably stupid.

01:19:36.388 --> 01:19:39.012
And then one night, he...
he messaged me back

01:19:39.044 --> 01:19:41.411
saying that...
that Monica was out of the house

01:19:41.444 --> 01:19:43.556
and I should come over
and we could talk about us.

01:19:43.588 --> 01:19:46.051
And before I can even ring
the bell,

01:19:46.083 --> 01:19:49.444
Monica opens the door
and tells me to come inside.

01:19:49.477 --> 01:19:50.979
She's holding his phone.

01:19:51.011 --> 01:19:53.221
She's the one who messaged me
to come over.

01:19:53.252 --> 01:19:57.988
She tells me Alastair's
passed out in the study and...

01:19:58.021 --> 01:20:00.740
she wanted to see who it was.

01:20:00.771 --> 01:20:02.821
When she found out
it was her daughter's teacher,

01:20:02.852 --> 01:20:05.379
she got pretty unhinged.

01:20:05.797 --> 01:20:08.195
Kept talking about...

01:20:09.155 --> 01:20:13.028
...how L.A. was this evil city
and...

01:20:13.059 --> 01:20:15.811
what a mistake it was
coming to L.A.

01:20:16.803 --> 01:20:20.611
I was scared
she was gonna get violent, so...

01:20:20.643 --> 01:20:21.891
I just ran out of there.

01:20:21.925 --> 01:20:22.916
I drove away.

01:20:24.419 --> 01:20:25.861
And then...

01:20:27.428 --> 01:20:30.692
...the next day,
I heard Monica was dead.

01:20:31.299 --> 01:20:34.244
And I tried reaching out
to Alastair,

01:20:34.275 --> 01:20:37.540
but... he was even more
of an asshole.

01:20:37.572 --> 01:20:39.811
He wouldn't talk to me,

01:20:39.843 --> 01:20:42.308
not even when he was
dropping Gaby off.

01:20:43.844 --> 01:20:45.668
So...

01:20:46.531 --> 01:20:50.275
Well, when the... when the chips
started falling on him...

01:20:53.892 --> 01:20:56.291
...I just let them fall.

01:20:59.684 --> 01:21:02.948
And you're pregnant?

01:21:02.979 --> 01:21:04.100
Alastair's?

01:21:08.932 --> 01:21:11.876
Jayne?
We're about to start.

01:21:12.836 --> 01:21:14.275
Yeah.

01:21:14.852 --> 01:21:16.388
Be right there.

01:21:16.419 --> 01:21:18.692
Can we pick this up later?

01:21:20.228 --> 01:21:22.660
After the play and lawyers.

01:21:27.172 --> 01:21:30.212
There's her necklace
and her ring.

01:21:30.244 --> 01:21:33.892
Next I'll take the child
as the king!

01:21:33.925 --> 01:21:35.845
Today I brew.

01:21:35.876 --> 01:21:37.892
Tomorrow I bake.

01:21:37.924 --> 01:21:42.147
And then the prince child
I'll take!

01:21:42.179 --> 01:21:44.772
For no one knows
my little game,

01:21:44.804 --> 01:21:47.524
and Rumpelstiltskin is my name!

01:21:48.580 --> 01:21:51.205
To guess my name?

01:21:51.236 --> 01:21:55.204
She'll never guess!

01:22:03.812 --> 01:22:05.668
Jayne?

01:22:45.603 --> 01:22:47.588
That girl from "Louisiana Law."

01:22:47.619 --> 01:22:49.539
What's her name? Yeah.
I need you to call her agent.

01:22:49.571 --> 01:22:50.980
I mean, is she pregnant
or is it...

01:22:51.012 --> 01:22:53.283
I don't know. She's unhappy?
'Cause it's weird.

01:22:53.315 --> 01:22:54.788
I mean,
I don't know if she changed

01:22:54.820 --> 01:22:57.540
what she's eating, but...

01:22:57.572 --> 01:22:59.236
You tell me.

01:22:59.268 --> 01:23:00.931
But they're feeding her
something very, very strange,

01:23:00.963 --> 01:23:02.915
'cause I have never seen a shape
quite like that.

01:23:03.524 --> 01:23:04.964
Waddling through the lot.

01:23:04.996 --> 01:23:06.691
And I-I was like,

01:23:06.723 --> 01:23:09.892
"It's not gonna work.
I don't want to look at that."

01:23:10.595 --> 01:23:11.845
All right.
Well, you tell him.

01:23:11.876 --> 01:23:12.932
All right. Bye.

01:23:12.964 --> 01:23:13.924
Mr. Waldo!

01:23:13.956 --> 01:23:15.620
Mr. Sikorsky.

01:23:15.652 --> 01:23:18.532
Apologies for the interruption,
but I made some progress.

01:23:18.565 --> 01:23:20.772
Oh, you did?
Fantastic.

01:23:20.804 --> 01:23:21.955
What is that?

01:23:21.987 --> 01:23:23.492
That, my friend, is signed

01:23:23.524 --> 01:23:26.404
by every quarterback
who ever won two Super Bowls.

01:23:26.436 --> 01:23:27.715
May I?

01:23:27.747 --> 01:23:29.156
Please.
Be my guest.

01:23:29.188 --> 01:23:32.005
May I also say it is so good
to see your baby face

01:23:32.036 --> 01:23:33.860
peeking out
where once a dead animal lay.

01:23:33.892 --> 01:23:35.876
And just when you thought I
couldn't get any more handsome.

01:23:35.908 --> 01:23:39.844
I have a run-through, but, um...
fuck 'em.

01:23:39.876 --> 01:23:41.892
I want to hear this.
Shoot.

01:23:41.924 --> 01:23:44.292
It's good news, I guess.

01:23:44.324 --> 01:23:45.604
I know who killed Monica Pinch.

01:23:45.636 --> 01:23:46.979
Fantastic.

01:23:47.011 --> 01:23:49.285
I mean...

01:23:49.316 --> 01:23:50.532
Mm.

01:23:50.564 --> 01:23:53.252
There's a young lady
named Jayne White.

01:23:53.860 --> 01:23:56.196
She was the Pinch girl's
kindergarten teacher.

01:23:56.228 --> 01:23:59.587
What'd a kindergarten teacher
want to kill Monica Pinch for?

01:23:59.620 --> 01:24:01.668
She and Alastair were having
an affair.

01:24:03.812 --> 01:24:05.540
You don't look surprised.

01:24:05.572 --> 01:24:07.139
They had a complicated marriage.

01:24:07.171 --> 01:24:09.220
Well, you knew them pretty well.

01:24:09.252 --> 01:24:11.652
Knew them well.
We did St. Bart's last year.

01:24:11.684 --> 01:24:15.108
I'm just so fuckin' relieved
it's not Alastair, you know?

01:24:15.140 --> 01:24:16.771
- I'm sure you are.
- I knew you were my guy.

01:24:16.803 --> 01:24:18.148
Fontella said,
"Don't hire that bum.

01:24:18.180 --> 01:24:19.876
He stinks in every way."

01:24:19.908 --> 01:24:22.020
But I was like, "No.
That's my guy."

01:24:22.052 --> 01:24:23.780
And do I know casting
or do I know casting?

01:24:23.812 --> 01:24:25.443
Is this chick in custody?

01:24:25.475 --> 01:24:26.724
Are we good?

01:24:26.756 --> 01:24:28.612
- Jayne?
- Yeah.

01:24:28.644 --> 01:24:29.892
No.

01:24:29.924 --> 01:24:31.748
- No. She left town.
- Ah, we'll find her.

01:24:31.780 --> 01:24:34.276
She's a fuckin' kindergarten
teacher, not Whitey Bulger.

01:24:34.308 --> 01:24:36.196
That's a win-win for Waldo
and Sikorsky.

01:24:36.228 --> 01:24:38.532
You get the killer.
I get to keep my syndication.

01:24:38.564 --> 01:24:42.595
I mean, it's a tragedy, but,
you know, as tragedies go...

01:24:42.627 --> 01:24:43.812
- Mm.
- But thank you.

01:24:43.844 --> 01:24:45.092
You know, great job and...

01:24:45.124 --> 01:24:46.820
Did you know Jayne White?

01:24:48.644 --> 01:24:49.988
I know <i>of</i> her.

01:24:50.020 --> 01:24:51.972
Did you know that Alastair
had gotten her pregnant?

01:24:52.004 --> 01:24:53.732
- Hey.
- I'm just wondering

01:24:53.764 --> 01:24:55.620
if that was something
many people were aware of.

01:24:55.652 --> 01:24:58.116
Many people? No.
This is inner-circle stuff.

01:24:58.148 --> 01:25:00.228
Right, but...
you're in the inner circle.

01:25:00.260 --> 01:25:02.020
I <i>founded</i> the inner circle.

01:25:02.052 --> 01:25:04.004
You know, he knows what I'm
doing, if you know what I mean.

01:25:04.036 --> 01:25:05.860
I know what he's doing,
if you know what I mean.

01:25:05.892 --> 01:25:07.236
So what was Monica Pinch's
reaction

01:25:07.268 --> 01:25:08.996
when she found out
Jayne White was pregnant?

01:25:09.028 --> 01:25:10.756
- She was devastated.
- I bet.

01:25:10.788 --> 01:25:12.548
I mean, she probably
pushed Alastair even harder

01:25:12.580 --> 01:25:14.020
to quit the show
and move back to England.

01:25:14.052 --> 01:25:15.684
I can't speak to that
'cause I don't know her

01:25:15.716 --> 01:25:18.340
- as well as I know him.
- Right.

01:25:18.372 --> 01:25:20.164
But you knew about the awards.

01:25:20.196 --> 01:25:22.019
The Shakespeare Awards
you talked about?

01:25:22.051 --> 01:25:23.428
They're called Regis,
by the way.

01:25:23.460 --> 01:25:24.835
What did you say?

01:25:24.867 --> 01:25:27.332
You said they were all
under the bed.

01:25:27.364 --> 01:25:28.932
Under the bed, in the attic.
Doesn't matter.

01:25:28.964 --> 01:25:30.020
He just didn't want them around.

01:25:30.052 --> 01:25:31.716
Ah. Gotcha.
It's funny.

01:25:31.748 --> 01:25:33.860
- They <i>were</i> under the bed.
- So?

01:25:33.892 --> 01:25:35.748
It's just Alastair said
he wasn't sure where they were.

01:25:35.780 --> 01:25:37.444
- It's not a big deal.
- Listen.

01:25:37.476 --> 01:25:39.876
This is great chatting with you,
but time is not my friend.

01:25:39.908 --> 01:25:41.540
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.
I'll let you go.

01:25:41.572 --> 01:25:43.075
Thanks.

01:25:43.107 --> 01:25:44.099
Monica Pinch.

01:25:44.580 --> 01:25:46.500
- Quickly.
- Monica Pinch.

01:25:46.532 --> 01:25:49.092
Now, she didn't find out
that Jayne White was pregnant

01:25:49.124 --> 01:25:50.372
until the night she died.

01:25:50.404 --> 01:25:52.324
So if she talked to you
about it,

01:25:52.356 --> 01:25:54.116
it must have been then, right?

01:25:54.148 --> 01:25:59.780
Uh, I'm gonna have to back you
up a second there, Mr. Waldo.

01:26:01.379 --> 01:26:03.524
You said that Jayne White
was the murderer.

01:26:03.556 --> 01:26:06.211
Oh, no. I said I knew
who the murderer was.

01:26:06.244 --> 01:26:09.027
Oh!

01:26:09.699 --> 01:26:11.300
Warren Gomes.

01:26:11.332 --> 01:26:12.867
Does that name mean anything
to you?

01:26:13.284 --> 01:26:15.172
- No.
- Well, he was this lawyer.

01:26:15.204 --> 01:26:16.771
I had a little bit
of a weird thing with him.

01:26:16.804 --> 01:26:18.339
He kept following me
for a couple days,

01:26:18.372 --> 01:26:21.156
and I kind of lost my temper
and I confronted him one day.

01:26:21.188 --> 01:26:22.564
We got into a little fight.

01:26:22.596 --> 01:26:23.844
A couple hours later,
he got killed.

01:26:23.876 --> 01:26:25.315
Yeah?

01:26:25.347 --> 01:26:26.788
I'm just trying to piece
everything together.

01:26:26.820 --> 01:26:29.380
The question is...
why bring it up...

01:26:29.412 --> 01:26:31.300
he had the same kind of watch
as you.

01:26:31.332 --> 01:26:32.676
Rich lawyer.

01:26:32.708 --> 01:26:34.308
That's what I thought.
Only I researched them.

01:26:34.340 --> 01:26:35.971
They'll all individually made,
right?

01:26:36.004 --> 01:26:37.763
No two are identical.

01:26:38.212 --> 01:26:40.004
Here's the thing...
The one he was wearing,

01:26:40.036 --> 01:26:42.595
- it looked a lot like yours.
- Pure coincidence.

01:26:42.627 --> 01:26:44.900
This one hasn't left my wrist
except when I shower and sleep.

01:26:44.932 --> 01:26:46.756
But you asked Fontella
what time it was.

01:26:46.787 --> 01:26:48.099
What? When?

01:26:48.132 --> 01:26:50.371
At the courthouse
after Alastair's arraignment.

01:26:50.404 --> 01:26:52.484
I'm afraid you must be mistaken.

01:26:52.516 --> 01:26:53.572
But, uh...

01:26:53.604 --> 01:26:55.140
Oh, fuck it.

01:26:55.171 --> 01:26:56.324
Take a seat.

01:26:56.356 --> 01:26:57.636
I want to hear everything
you're thinking,

01:26:57.668 --> 01:26:58.915
soup to nuts, all right?

01:26:58.948 --> 01:27:00.484
- Soup to nuts?
- Yes, please.

01:27:00.516 --> 01:27:02.948
- Double-fuck the read-through.
- Let's do that. Let's do it.

01:27:02.980 --> 01:27:04.036
- You sure?
- Yes, sir.

01:27:04.964 --> 01:27:06.595
Buckle up.

01:27:09.124 --> 01:27:10.787
Well, I'm thinking...

01:27:12.420 --> 01:27:16.388
...that you knew what
Monica Pinch kept under her bed

01:27:16.420 --> 01:27:18.180
'cause you were spending time
in her bedroom

01:27:18.211 --> 01:27:20.356
while Alastair was spending time
with Jayne.

01:27:23.652 --> 01:27:25.028
Mr. Waldo!

01:27:25.060 --> 01:27:26.884
That is brilliant.

01:27:28.356 --> 01:27:30.756
I'm thinking
that on the night she found out

01:27:30.788 --> 01:27:33.732
that he'd gotten Jayne pregnant,
with Alastair passed out cold,

01:27:33.764 --> 01:27:35.780
I'm thinking
that Monica called you

01:27:35.812 --> 01:27:38.468
to tell you she was gonna
tell Alastair about your affair

01:27:38.500 --> 01:27:39.972
to get him to quit the show
and move back to England,

01:27:40.004 --> 01:27:41.412
like she'd been wanting.

01:27:41.444 --> 01:27:42.756
But you couldn't afford
to lose Alastair,

01:27:42.788 --> 01:27:44.739
not with the Jamshidi
takeover threat.

01:27:44.772 --> 01:27:47.971
I'm thinking that you drove
over there.

01:27:48.388 --> 01:27:50.180
You were gonna talk some sense
into Monica.

01:27:50.212 --> 01:27:51.811
But she didn't want to hear it.

01:27:51.844 --> 01:27:53.124
Next thing,
you guys are arguing.

01:27:53.156 --> 01:27:55.012
It escalates,
and you pick up the Regis Award.

01:27:55.044 --> 01:27:56.259
And you hit her with it.

01:27:56.867 --> 01:27:58.884
You didn't mean to do it.
It's an act of passion.

01:27:58.916 --> 01:28:00.996
Thing is, she's hit her head
on the way down,

01:28:01.028 --> 01:28:02.724
and now she's not moving.

01:28:02.756 --> 01:28:04.868
So you panic,
and you start wiping down

01:28:04.899 --> 01:28:06.436
everything you can remember
touching.

01:28:06.467 --> 01:28:08.484
But the Regis Award
was on a wooden table,

01:28:08.516 --> 01:28:10.244
and that had bloodstains on it.

01:28:10.276 --> 01:28:12.964
Now, I'm thinking...
I'm just thinking...

01:28:12.996 --> 01:28:16.004
maybe you were worried that
some of that was your blood.

01:28:16.036 --> 01:28:18.148
You could've got cut
in the fight.

01:28:18.180 --> 01:28:19.780
So now what do you do?

01:28:19.811 --> 01:28:21.860
You swap around some furniture.

01:28:21.892 --> 01:28:23.524
You set the alarm
on the way out.

01:28:23.556 --> 01:28:25.348
You get rid of the Regis
in some dumpster,

01:28:25.380 --> 01:28:30.244
and you let poor old Alastair
wake up to take the rap.

01:28:30.596 --> 01:28:32.196
How did I do?

01:28:36.964 --> 01:28:38.499
Come on.

01:28:38.532 --> 01:28:40.323
And the lawyer guy?
What...

01:28:40.356 --> 01:28:42.148
He blackmailed you.

01:28:42.180 --> 01:28:44.036
He even made you cough up
that fancy watch,

01:28:44.068 --> 01:28:47.076
which you couldn't resist
taking back after you shot him.

01:28:48.099 --> 01:28:49.444
Huh?

01:28:51.331 --> 01:28:53.859
That is quite brilliant.

01:28:53.892 --> 01:28:56.260
In fact, I should give you
a pilot deal.

01:28:56.291 --> 01:28:58.307
There <i>is</i> one gaping hole
in your narrative, however.

01:28:58.340 --> 01:29:01.316
Why would I sabotage the biggest
asset on this network?

01:29:01.348 --> 01:29:02.884
Come on.
That's the easy part.

01:29:02.916 --> 01:29:04.164
You told me yourself

01:29:04.196 --> 01:29:06.084
the scandal made the show
twice as valuable.

01:29:06.116 --> 01:29:07.876
You knew Alastair would get off.

01:29:07.907 --> 01:29:09.827
I mean, it's L.A.
The star always gets off.

01:29:09.860 --> 01:29:12.580
And in the meantime,
the more publicity,

01:29:12.611 --> 01:29:14.019
the bigger the windfall.

01:29:14.052 --> 01:29:15.587
So what do you do?

01:29:15.620 --> 01:29:18.148
You hire the lawyer
who'll make the most noise

01:29:18.180 --> 01:29:20.196
and then the detective
who would make the most noise,

01:29:20.228 --> 01:29:22.404
even though your lawyer
kept telling you

01:29:22.436 --> 01:29:24.260
I'd be a shitty choice.

01:29:24.292 --> 01:29:25.988
And let's be honest.
I <i>am</i> a shitty choice.

01:29:26.020 --> 01:29:28.196
I've never been a P.I.
The LAPD fucking hates me.

01:29:28.227 --> 01:29:31.332
I'm so rusty,
I'd probably be useless.

01:29:31.364 --> 01:29:34.083
But I think you liked me
for those reasons.

01:29:35.139 --> 01:29:36.932
'Cause that made me
the last detective

01:29:36.963 --> 01:29:40.644
who'd ever figure out
that you killed Monica Pinch.

01:29:41.796 --> 01:29:43.044
<i>And</i> Warren Gomes.

01:29:46.532 --> 01:29:48.964
A lot of moving parts.

01:29:50.307 --> 01:29:52.356
A lot of moving parts.

01:29:55.811 --> 01:29:58.083
I do have one question.

01:29:58.116 --> 01:30:01.732
What made you so sure

01:30:01.764 --> 01:30:04.612
that you walk in here
and deliver that little pitch?

01:30:07.268 --> 01:30:09.412
I'll be honest.

01:30:09.444 --> 01:30:11.588
I only walked in 98% sure.

01:30:11.619 --> 01:30:12.964
Ah.

01:30:16.067 --> 01:30:17.891
What was the other 2%?

01:30:17.924 --> 01:30:20.708
I had to make sure
you were a lefty.

01:30:24.644 --> 01:30:26.883
I did make one mistake, though.

01:30:26.916 --> 01:30:30.756
I really should've waited
until the cops got here.

01:30:30.788 --> 01:30:33.124
You... You told them to come?

01:30:33.155 --> 01:30:35.396
Well, if I timed it right,
they're already downstairs.

01:30:35.427 --> 01:30:39.140
Of course...
I don't have a watch.

01:30:41.124 --> 01:30:42.884
After you.

01:30:42.916 --> 01:30:46.531
Yeah. You just keep smiling.

01:30:46.564 --> 01:30:48.548
Watch your haircut.

01:30:49.956 --> 01:30:52.228
Come on.
Look alive, fellas.

01:30:52.260 --> 01:30:53.796
Pete couldn't make it himself?

01:30:53.828 --> 01:30:55.524
You know he's not gonna let you
out of this collar, right?

01:30:55.556 --> 01:30:57.155
I'm gonna head
to North Hollywood.

01:30:57.188 --> 01:30:58.532
Tell Pete I'll meet him there.

01:30:59.300 --> 01:31:01.316
See you in court!

01:31:01.347 --> 01:31:03.236
What are you doing?!

01:31:03.267 --> 01:31:05.891
Get off my bike!

01:31:05.924 --> 01:31:07.748
We're not cops, man.
We're... We're extras.

01:31:07.780 --> 01:31:09.027
Shut the fuck up.

01:31:12.740 --> 01:31:15.556
Fuck! Fuck!

01:31:33.924 --> 01:31:38.435
<i>Ho ho ho! Merry Christmas!</i>

01:32:53.924 --> 01:32:55.204
Fuck!

01:33:03.044 --> 01:33:04.739
...Lady Justice.

01:33:04.771 --> 01:33:07.107
Make sure that
he isn't prejudiced

01:33:07.140 --> 01:33:09.220
or predispositioned...

01:33:09.253 --> 01:33:11.491
Fuck!

01:33:11.524 --> 01:33:14.020
"For 99 days, you do that,

01:33:14.053 --> 01:33:17.571
and justice, in its natural
wisdom, will find its own way.

01:33:17.604 --> 01:33:19.268
But, Johnnie," he'd say...

01:33:20.387 --> 01:33:22.436
"...on the 100th day,

01:33:22.467 --> 01:33:27.397
a great judge knows
that he needs to <i>be</i> justice."

01:33:29.060 --> 01:33:31.748
- Ready for your close-up?
- Wait! Wait!

01:33:31.780 --> 01:33:33.253
"...I do know
that as I sit here today..."

01:33:33.284 --> 01:33:35.395
How are you gonna get away
with this?

01:33:35.428 --> 01:33:37.891
A light fell on set.
Happens all the time.

01:33:37.924 --> 01:33:39.555
Last looks.

01:33:42.788 --> 01:33:46.564
...and find
this here defendant... guilty.

01:33:57.700 --> 01:34:00.548
What the fuck?
This place is fallin' apart.

01:34:00.997 --> 01:34:02.564
Waldo.

01:34:02.595 --> 01:34:04.291
Hey, Q.

01:34:11.939 --> 01:34:14.276
- Well, that's that, then.
- Yeah.

01:34:14.307 --> 01:34:16.739
Would it be ungrateful
to ask what you're doing here?

01:34:16.771 --> 01:34:19.971
I've been following you
since the recruiting office.

01:34:20.004 --> 01:34:22.820
I even had to sit through
that Rumpelstiltskin bullshit.

01:34:22.851 --> 01:34:24.579
- Really?
- Yeah.

01:34:25.444 --> 01:34:26.980
How'd you get on the lot?

01:34:27.013 --> 01:34:29.828
Snuck in on a studio tour.
Yeah.

01:34:29.860 --> 01:34:31.524
They really need to check out
their security.

01:34:31.556 --> 01:34:34.693
I could be, like, a crazy
stalker or something, you know?

01:34:34.724 --> 01:34:37.477
I, uh, hope you don't mind.
I used your gun.

01:34:38.468 --> 01:34:40.771
I was never here.

01:34:40.804 --> 01:34:41.987
Yeah.
I can work with that.

01:34:42.788 --> 01:34:44.164
Grand.

01:34:45.188 --> 01:34:47.715
You do know why I saved
your ass, right?

01:34:48.771 --> 01:34:50.884
- Yeah, I got an idea.
- Mm.

01:34:53.379 --> 01:34:55.556
Someone else kills you first,
I can't get what I want.

01:34:55.588 --> 01:34:57.028
It'll be a mess.

01:34:57.059 --> 01:34:58.660
Nobody will know what to do
with themselves.

01:34:58.693 --> 01:35:02.147
You know, I got to say, Q,
it's not too clever

01:35:02.180 --> 01:35:04.771
keeping your kind of business
records on a flash drive.

01:35:04.804 --> 01:35:07.011
Is that what Cuppy thinks
is on there?

01:35:07.684 --> 01:35:09.157
Business records.

01:35:09.188 --> 01:35:12.548
The guy's an idiot.

01:35:12.579 --> 01:35:16.195
Why?
What <i>is</i> on there?

01:35:16.228 --> 01:35:17.732
Epic poem.

01:35:19.108 --> 01:35:21.059
Long-ass motherfucker, too.

01:35:21.091 --> 01:35:23.108
It's the only copy I got.

01:35:23.139 --> 01:35:25.091
Epic poem that you wrote?

01:35:25.124 --> 01:35:26.533
Yeah, that I wrote.

01:35:26.564 --> 01:35:28.804
- Ah.
- It's about the life of a dealer

01:35:28.835 --> 01:35:30.659
trying to retain
his independence and integrity

01:35:30.691 --> 01:35:33.475
in an era
of corporate-style cartels.

01:35:33.956 --> 01:35:35.876
Why an epic poem?

01:35:35.908 --> 01:35:38.308
See, me, I'm an autodidact.

01:35:38.339 --> 01:35:41.348
Means I'm self-educated.
I had to enrich my own life.

01:35:41.379 --> 01:35:44.740
But my little girl, Dulcy...

01:35:44.772 --> 01:35:48.421
I'm gonna make sure my daughter
gets a real education.

01:35:48.452 --> 01:35:52.004
That way, she ain't stuck
being no cop, no dealer.

01:35:52.035 --> 01:35:53.924
I want to give the poem to her

01:35:53.955 --> 01:35:56.132
so she can see the man
I really am.

01:35:57.731 --> 01:35:59.876
Waldo, I need my mem.

01:35:59.908 --> 01:36:03.781
I need Lorena to come back,
so...

01:36:03.812 --> 01:36:05.507
I'll tell you what.

01:36:05.540 --> 01:36:06.788
I want you to get my little girl

01:36:06.820 --> 01:36:09.251
into that fancy-ass
private school.

01:36:09.284 --> 01:36:11.300
Same one as that
British dude's kid.

01:36:11.971 --> 01:36:14.500
Get him to help Dulcy
and bring me back my mem,

01:36:14.532 --> 01:36:16.675
and Lorena can come back.

01:36:16.708 --> 01:36:18.788
Have you got the juice for that?

01:36:18.819 --> 01:36:21.668
You know, I just might.

01:36:24.132 --> 01:36:28.323
Okay, Waldo.
You got another 24 hours.

01:36:30.148 --> 01:36:33.923
By the way,
I love Johnnie's bench.

01:36:39.397 --> 01:36:41.027
You know,

01:36:41.060 --> 01:36:43.012
my granddaddy once said...

01:36:47.172 --> 01:36:50.468
"...It's one thing to write
like a poet...

01:36:50.948 --> 01:36:54.435
...and another thing altogether
to write like a historian.

01:36:57.284 --> 01:37:01.285
A poet can rehash
or sing about things

01:37:01.316 --> 01:37:05.125
not like they were
but like they should have been.

01:37:07.748 --> 01:37:09.508
And the historian...

01:37:10.820 --> 01:37:12.132
...well, he's got to write
about them

01:37:12.164 --> 01:37:13.732
not like they
should have been..."

01:37:13.765 --> 01:37:15.395
Fuckin' Lorena.

01:37:15.428 --> 01:37:17.507
"...but like they were...

01:37:19.203 --> 01:37:22.660
...without adding or subtracting
anything from the truth."

01:37:24.068 --> 01:37:25.444
And might I remind you,
Counselor,

01:37:25.476 --> 01:37:28.835
you're getting dangerously close
to rufflin' my feathers.

01:37:28.868 --> 01:37:30.691
Do you understand the words
"contempt of court"?

01:37:31.811 --> 01:37:33.124
Come in.

01:37:34.212 --> 01:37:36.772
Aha!
The man of the hour.

01:37:36.805 --> 01:37:39.652
Come here.
Deftly done, my old cockalorum.

01:37:39.685 --> 01:37:40.932
No tongues.

01:37:40.964 --> 01:37:42.756
Come in. Sit down.
Sit.

01:37:42.788 --> 01:37:45.123
I want to lavish praise on you.

01:37:46.628 --> 01:37:48.580
Is it too much of a cliché
to say...

01:37:48.612 --> 01:37:50.276
I don't know how to thank you?

01:37:50.308 --> 01:37:52.931
Is it too much of a cliché
to say I might have an idea?

01:37:52.964 --> 01:37:54.915
- Shoot.
- I'm thinking you were right

01:37:54.948 --> 01:37:56.804
about that epic
two-week pub crawl.

01:37:56.835 --> 01:37:58.084
That's a brilliant idea.

01:37:58.116 --> 01:38:00.068
Unfortunately, as of today...

01:38:02.948 --> 01:38:06.339
...this is my liquor of choice.

01:38:08.228 --> 01:38:09.476
- Sober as a judge.
- Yes.

01:38:09.508 --> 01:38:11.556
Very good.

01:38:11.588 --> 01:38:13.381
I may drop dead any second,

01:38:13.412 --> 01:38:15.332
but at least now
I'm not inviting it.

01:38:16.324 --> 01:38:18.788
I made a shambles of everything,
Waldo.

01:38:18.819 --> 01:38:20.515
Monica's gone.

01:38:20.547 --> 01:38:23.140
Jayne's run off with her son
or daughter... I may never know.

01:38:24.387 --> 01:38:28.227
On the other hand,
I do have my sweet Gaby.

01:38:28.259 --> 01:38:29.508
And the least I owe her

01:38:29.540 --> 01:38:31.460
is the best I have.

01:38:31.492 --> 01:38:34.083
That could take more courage
than drinking yourself to death.

01:38:34.115 --> 01:38:36.580
Don't I know it.

01:38:37.381 --> 01:38:38.819
Courage, mate.

01:38:38.851 --> 01:38:41.060
Cheers.

01:38:41.092 --> 01:38:43.268
- Ready for you, Mr. Pinch.
- Yes. Let's off.

01:38:43.876 --> 01:38:45.892
And, uh, don't tell anyone
about this.

01:38:45.925 --> 01:38:47.555
If they think I'm still a drunk,

01:38:47.588 --> 01:38:50.371
they'll still let me paste
the occasional pretty boy.

01:39:02.308 --> 01:39:04.196
I got your text.

01:39:05.667 --> 01:39:08.228
Thanks for squaring things
with Q.

01:39:08.260 --> 01:39:10.467
And yet all you talked about
was Pinch.

01:39:10.885 --> 01:39:12.900
I wanted you to do that, too.

01:39:12.932 --> 01:39:14.564
I hope I didn't cause you
too much trouble.

01:39:14.596 --> 01:39:17.572
Oh, not at all.
I made some new friends.

01:39:17.924 --> 01:39:19.492
Well, if you're up for it,

01:39:19.525 --> 01:39:21.188
I've got something else
we could work together.

01:39:21.219 --> 01:39:23.043
You know,
I don't think my face can take

01:39:23.075 --> 01:39:24.068
much more of your action.

01:39:24.099 --> 01:39:25.348
Oh, stop being such a princess.

01:39:25.380 --> 01:39:27.811
You know you loved
every minute of it.

01:39:28.771 --> 01:39:30.052
You look good.

01:39:30.085 --> 01:39:32.036
Yeah.
You look pretty good yourself...

01:39:32.068 --> 01:39:33.475
for a dead woman.

01:39:33.507 --> 01:39:34.756
How'd you pull that off?

01:39:34.788 --> 01:39:36.964
A coroner down in San Berdoo
owed me a favor.

01:39:36.996 --> 01:39:38.852
They let me have a Jane Doe
they were gonna cremate.

01:39:38.884 --> 01:39:41.251
So I burned her
in my ex-husband's car.

01:39:41.283 --> 01:39:42.532
Ex-husband?

01:39:42.565 --> 01:39:44.995
- Almost ex.
- Mm.

01:39:45.572 --> 01:39:47.620
What, you want me to tell you
if it what bothers me

01:39:47.652 --> 01:39:50.052
that you got married?

01:39:50.084 --> 01:39:52.100
I don't need you to tell me.

01:39:54.627 --> 01:39:57.156
And you disappeared on me.
I don't owe you anything.

01:39:57.188 --> 01:39:58.788
Hey, I didn't say you did.

01:39:58.820 --> 01:40:00.805
Why don't you tell me
what happened to your beard?

01:40:02.916 --> 01:40:04.420
Who was she?

01:40:04.452 --> 01:40:05.572
You were dead.

01:40:05.605 --> 01:40:07.492
Barely!
My body wasn't even cold.

01:40:07.525 --> 01:40:08.485
I was grieving.

01:40:08.516 --> 01:40:11.140
Oh, you know what?
Fuck it.

01:40:12.963 --> 01:40:15.332
So that's it? You just breeze in
and breeze back out?

01:40:15.364 --> 01:40:17.092
You ghosted me for three years.

01:40:17.125 --> 01:40:19.876
Then I drive up your stupid
mountain, and you're Ice Man.

01:40:19.908 --> 01:40:21.924
Then you come out here,
one week in L.A.,

01:40:21.956 --> 01:40:23.812
